[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    137[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mThis recipe builds directly on Recipe 4.4. The patient-profile DynamoDB table from 4.1, extended in 4.4, gets new attributes ([38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mpharmacy_data_quality[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mcash_pay_history[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mcost_sharing_tier[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mmed_sync_enrolled[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m). The engagement-event Kinesis stream gets new event types ([38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140madherence_intervention_recommended[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mintervention_engaged[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mintervention_completed[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mpharmacy_fill_observed[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mbarrier_elicited[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m). The SageMaker Feature Store features defined in 4.4 are reused; new features are added for medication-specific signals (per-medication PDC, days since last fill, cost-sharing for the specific drug, formulary tier, days-supply pattern).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    138[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    139[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mThe uplift-modeling investment from 4.4 transfers directly. The capacity-aware allocator gains a multi-intervention-per-patient mode and a per-intervention-capacity model. The cohort fairness instrumentation from 4.3 and 4.4 becomes more important here because adherence outcomes have well-documented disparities by race, language, geography, and socioeconomic status, and a poorly-built recommender will encode those disparities into its targeting. Recipe 4.6 (Care Gap Prioritization) and Recipe 4.7 (Care Management Program Enrollment) reuse this recipe's barrier-classification and multi-intervention scoring patterns.[K
